about that?

00:27:10.570 --> 00:27:12.340
&gt;&gt;Janice Bell: I can talk a lot about that.
I'm not sure you'd wanna hear it.

00:27:12.340 --> 00:27:16.580
By the way, it's not covered in my book because
active and passive voice, I'm glad you called

00:27:16.580 --> 00:27:21.000
it "voice" and not "tense." Usually people
call it "tense" which is isn't, are matters

00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:25.490
of style. This is style were talking about
here. The active voice is correct and the

00:27:25.490 --> 00:27:31.070
passive voice is correct and you know what
else these days there's, there's not a huge

00:27:31.070 --> 00:27:35.110
problem of people using the passive when they
should be using the active. We've sort of

00:27:35.110 --> 00:27:37.070
come over that hump in our society.

00:27:37.070 --> 00:27:42.141
When I began teaching writing in organizations
and in businesses, the passive voice was all

00:27:42.141 --> 00:27:45.710
too prevalent and now it's really not. So
we can prove.

00:27:45.710 --> 00:27:51.120
For those of you who are sitting there thinking,
"What the heck are they talking about?" Anytime

00:27:51.120 --> 00:27:56.910
you have an idea you're going to have a subject
and a verb, even the simplest of ideas. You

00:27:56.910 --> 00:28:01.460
know, "The dog ate the bone." You've got somebody
at the beginning and you have an action happening.

00:28:01.460 --> 00:28:08.040
If that somebody at the beginning is doing
the action, and by the way, tense has nothing

00:28:08.040 --> 00:28:11.810
to do with this, it doesn't matter whether
"the dog ate the bone yesterday," whether

00:28:11.810 --> 00:28:16.260
"he is eating it presently," whether he "will"
eat it tomorrow, or whether he "had" eaten

00:28:16.260 --> 00:28:22.560
it before I did something else. That dog is
the agent of the action regardless of when

00:28:22.560 --> 00:28:28.120
it took place. That whole idea is said to
be written in the active voice.

00:28:28.120 --> 00:28:33.010
So, "The dog ate the bone" is active. It also
has nothing to do with meaning. If I say,

00:28:33.010 --> 00:28:39.040
"The man lay dead on the floor" that's active.
People go, "But, but he's dead." I told you

00:28:39.040 --> 00:28:43.020
it had nothin' to do with meaning. Did the
man do the lying on the floor? Did the man

00:28:43.020 --> 00:28:49.640
lie on the floor? I said "the man lay." "Lay"
why, because that's the past tense of "l-i-e"

00:28:49.640 --> 00:28:51.230
believe it or not. That's in my book too.

00:28:51.230 --> 00:28:54.970
Anyhow. But that's an active sentence because
the man "did" the "lying" on the floor. The

00:28:54.970 --> 00:28:57.590
man did the action.

00:28:57.590 --> 00:29:01.600
Whether the dog "eats the bone" now, "will
eat it tomorrow," or "did eat it yesterday,"

00:29:01.600 --> 00:29:03.140
he's doing the action; that's called active.

00:29:03.140 --> 00:29:09.490
If I turn it around and start that same idea
with the bone I'm gonna get what we call passive.

00:29:09.490 --> 00:29:11.440
And I'll tell you why in a moment.

00:29:11.440 --> 00:29:16.580
"The bone was eaten by the dog," same idea,
right? But now I've got the "bone" in the

00:29:16.580 --> 00:29:23.310
subject position. Grammatically it's the subject
and psychologically it's the subject. When

00:29:23.310 --> 00:29:27.550
I say, "The bone was eaten by the dog" you
should be getting the message that this sentence

00:29:27.550 --> 00:29:33.560
is about the bone. It's kind of incidental
that the guy who ate it is the dog, right?

00:29:33.560 --> 00:29:39.340
"The dog ate the bone." Subject: dog; focal
point: dog. "The bone was eaten by the dog."

00:29:39.340 --> 00:29:42.960
Subject: bone; focal point: bone, right?

00:29:42.960 --> 00:29:49.980
That's called passive because the new subject
"bone" didn't do the eating. "The bone was

00:29:49.980 --> 00:29:58.280
eaten." "It was considered." "It had been
decided." "It was recommended." You hear those?

00:29:58.280 --> 00:30:03.150
Those are typically passive constructions.
The subject of those last three examples is

00:30:03.150 --> 00:30:09.840
"it." And yet "it" didn't do the deciding
or the recommending or the considering, right?

00:30:09.840 --> 00:30:15.680
Who did? And this is why the gentlemen in
the back was told awhile back by teachers

00:30:15.680 --> 00:30:17.570
"avoid the passive voice."

00:30:17.570 --> 00:30:24.060
We don't always need to avoid the passive
voice. It's just that it's a lot better style

00:30:24.060 --> 00:30:30.300
to say "who recommended," "who decided," "who
considered" in the business world. And lately

00:30:30.300 --> 00:30:33.880
people know that and they're not hiding. They're
not saying, "It is recommended that something

00:30:33.880 --> 00:30:38.180
be done." They're saying, "Management recommends
that we do something," right? Isn't that more

00:30:38.180 --> 00:30:43.990
typical in the work environment now? Great.
We got over a, one problem in this society.

00:30:43.990 --> 00:30:48.500
So that's probably, well that's one of the
rea, reasons teachers were telling you to

00:30:48.500 --> 00:30:53.140
stay away from passivity. The other thing
is a passive idea, "The bone was eaten by

00:30:53.140 --> 00:30:59.451
the dog" always requires more words than an
active idea. "The dog ate the bone." You hear

00:30:59.451 --> 00:31:00.451
it?

00:31:00.451 --> 00:31:01.451
[pause]

00:31:01.451 --> 00:31:06.970
Five for "dog ate the bone;" seven for "The
bone was eaten by the dog."

00:31:06.970 --> 00:31:11.650
Because to create a passive verb you have
to add a "was" or an "is" or a "will be" before

00:31:11.650 --> 00:31:16.390
another verb. "Was eaten" versus "ate." And
then to tell who did it if you're gonna give

00:31:16.390 --> 00:31:20.860
all the information you've gotta add a little
"by" at the end.

00:31:20.860 --> 00:31:25.770
Now passivity comes in handy however when
this whole paragraph's gonna be about the

00:31:25.770 --> 00:31:28.620
bone. And I don't mind telling you who ate
it, but I'm not gonna start by putting the

00:31:28.620 --> 00:31:33.970
